column3: I don't like the questions about first years (or even about individual students generally) because they are often hard for the group to answer during the clinic, they're often not that funny and they can make people feel singled out. Plus they're impossible to answer for older students who haven't interacted much with the first years. General questions about the dept (core courses, fyp, roz emails, research, faculty) seem more inclusive/relevant to everyone, I would advocate for only using these
